\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy establishes mandatory personnel security and background screening requirements for individuals granted logical or physical access to Elko County information systems,
 facilities containing IT assets,
 or County data.
 The policy minimizes insider risk and enforces compliance with federal Criminal Justice Information (CJI) personnel security requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all employees,
 elected officials,
 contractors,
 vendors,
 interns,
 and volunteers requiring logical or physical access to County IT resources.
 Standards apply across these classifications:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
General Access
\series default
:
 Access to systems or data not designated as CJI.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Privileged Access
\series default
:
 Elevated permissions (Role Tiers L3–L5) capable of altering system configurations or security controls.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJI Access
\series default
:
 Any role with potential unescorted access to unencrypted Criminal Justice Information (CJI).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Human Resources (HR)
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as the authoritative source for personnel status (hire,
 transfer,
 termination).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall notify Information Operations of personnel changes via the service desk or designated HRIS in accordance with the timelines defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall retain screening documentation for seven (7) years post-separation per Nevada local government retention schedules.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall define positions requiring Privileged or CJI Access screening.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as the final gatekeeper;
 access shall not be provisioned until HR confirms screening adjudication is "Cleared."
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Department Heads
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall identify roles requiring enhanced screening prior to recruitment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall ensure third-party personnel do not begin work until screening is adjudicated and access is formally approved.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All Personnel
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall truthfully disclose legal history during screening.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall report any personal arrest,
 criminal charge,
 or restraining order to HR within twenty-four (24) hours.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
No Clearance,
 No Access
\series default
:
 Access shall not be granted until screening and adjudication are complete for the applicable classification.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Universal Applicability
\series default
:
 These standards apply to the use of County IT resources at all times and in all locations,
 including remote work and official travel.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Sanctions
\series default
:
 Violations may result in access revocation,
 disciplinary action,
 and referral for civil or criminal enforcement under NRS 205.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Prohibited for CJI roles.
 For non-CJI roles,
 temporary exceptions require documented risk assessment,
 compensating controls (e.g.,
 constant physical escort),
 and written approval by the IT Director.
\end_layout

