\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1.
 Position Risk and Access Classification
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall assign each role an access classification (General,
 Privileged,
 or CJI).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Access classification mapping
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
General
\series default
:
 Expected user behavior;
 non-CJIS access.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Privileged
\series default
:
 IT Role Tiers L3–L5.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJI Access
\series default
:
 Any tier with potential unescorted access to unencrypted CJI.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2.
 Screening Requirements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
General Access
\series default
:
 Personnel shall complete County-required identity verification and background screening prior to access provisioning.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJI Access
\series default
:
 Personnel shall complete CJIS-required state of residency and national fingerprint-based record checks conducted through an FBI-approved authority 
\series bold
prior
\series default
 to access provisioning.
 No "pending" or temporary access is permitted for CJI environments.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3.
 CJI Adjudication Standards
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Felony Convictions
\series default
:
 If a felony conviction of any kind exists,
 the individual 
\series bold
shall be denied
\series default
 access to CJI.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Misdemeanors
\series default
:
 Access may be granted only if the LASO determines the nature of the offense does not warrant disqualification.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Fugitive Status
\series default
:
 Access shall be denied to any individual with an active warrant.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4.
 Continuous Vetting
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Re-screening
\series default
:
 Personnel with CJI Access shall undergo a full re-investigation (including fingerprints) every 
\series bold
five (5) years
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Self-Reporting
\series default
:
 Failure to self-report arrests or charges within 24 hours is grounds for immediate access revocation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5.
 Transfers and Termination Upon HR notification,
 Information Operations shall revoke or adjust access:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
High-Risk Individuals
\series default
:
 Accounts disabled within thirty (30) minutes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Involuntary Termination
\series default
:
 Accounts disabled within thirty (30) minutes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Standard Termination
\series default
:
 Accounts disabled within twenty-four (24) hours.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Transfers
\series default
:
 Access authorizations shall be modified within twenty-four (24) hours to align with the "Least Privilege" principle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6.
 Exit Requirements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Upon termination,
 HR or the Department Head shall conduct an exit interview covering non-disclosure obligations (NDA) regarding CJI and PII.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
All County-issued assets (badges,
 keys,
 tokens,
 devices) must be recovered prior to final departure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7.
 High-Risk Individual Definition
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
A "High-Risk Individual" includes anyone with:
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Involuntary/hostile termination
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Credible threat of misuse or retaliation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Formal notice of investigation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Discovery of direct threat to CJI confidentiality or integrity.
\end_layout

